title: Accessibility
description: In the two main short-term car parks, there are more than 90 parking spaces dedicated for use by passengers with reduced mobility. For Terminal 2, there are 40 spaces between levels 1 and 2 of the new multi-story car park. The parking spaces are specially treated with a non-slip surface, and are most convenient for wheelchair access. They are also clearly signposted. Disabled spaces are recommended to be pre-booked, as there are special rates available.

title: Accessibility
description: In the two main short-term car parks, there are more than 90 parking spaces dedicated for use by passengers with reduced mobility. For Terminal 1, there are fifty spaces available, located on the lower ground floor of Block B in front of the terminal building. The parking spaces are specially treated with a non-slip surface, and are most convenient for wheelchair access. They are also clearly signposted. Disabled spaces are recommended to be pre-booked, as there are special rates available.

title: Accessibility
description: The Long Term Red car park is serviced by a 24/7 wheelchair accessible shuttle bus service to and from the main passenger terminal.

title: Accessibility
description:
Fully accessible terminal building with specially adapted facilities including toilets and lifts, all clearly signposted. A series of induction loops facilitates the amplification of announcements for passengers with hearing difficulties. A counter loop system at the information desk facilitates clear communication with the information assistants on duty.

Should you need any assistance at the Airport, please do not hesitate to contact our Customer Relations Agents or any available staff member. You can also contact our Customer Relations Department on +353 1 814 4717.

title: Parking
description:
Blue Long Term Car Park
Long-term Parking Rates:
€4.95 per day if pre-booked or €7.50 per day if the drive up and park spaces are used.

Shuttle buses operate twenty-four hours a day, and are available every fifteen minutes.
More information about parking

title: Parking
description:
Red Long Term Car Park
Approximately five minutes away from the airport by shuttle bus. The shuttle buses stop at both terminals, nearby the departure areas. Shuttle transfers are available every eight minutes, and are vehicles which are able to accommodate wheelchair users.

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Bus Service
Dublin Airport is accessible by over 1,000 buses and coaches daily. From the airport, you can reach many areas in and around Dublin, as well as various towns and cities across Ireland.

title: Taxis and Public Transportation
description:
Taxi Service
Taxis are available from the forecourts directly outside Terminal 1 and Terminal 2. Passengers should follow Taxi signage to the designated taxi ranks.

title: Wi-Fi
description: Dublin Airport Terminal 1 is a free WiFi zone, offering wireless broadband service in Arrivals, Departures, the Mezzanine, The Street, and all the Departure gates.
